  • Constructor Details

    • ReactedSubmissionPublisher

      public ReactedSubmissionPublisher​(ReActorSystem localReActorSystem, java.lang.String feedName)
      Creates a location oblivious data publisher with backpressure. Subscribers can slowdown the producer or just drop data if they are best effort subscribers. Publisher is Serializable, so it can be sent to any reactor over any gate and subscribers can simply join the stream.
      Parameters:
      localReActorSystem - ReActorSystem used to manage and control the data flow
      feedName - Name of this feed. Feed name must be unique and if deterministic it allows cold replay

    • subscribe

      public void subscribe​(java.util.concurrent.Flow.Subscriber<? super PayloadT> subscriber, java.util.concurrent.Executor asyncBackpressurer, java.time.Duration backpressureErrorTimeout)
      + Registers a producer slowdown subscriber. Submissions towards this subscriber will be marked as completed only when the message has been actually delivered or on error, allowing the producer to slow down the production rate. Strict message ordering is guaranteed to be the same of submission
      Parameters:
      subscriber - Java Flow compliant subscriber
      backpressureErrorTimeout - the subscriber will try to deliver the message for at max this amount of time before signaling an error
      asyncBackpressurer - the executor to use for async delivery, supporting creation of at least one independent thread
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if duration is not bigger than zero
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if any of the arguments is null

    • subscribe

      public void subscribe​(java.util.concurrent.Flow.Subscriber<? super PayloadT> subscriber, int bufferSize, java.time.Duration backpressureTimeout, java.util.concurrent.Executor asyncBackpressurer, java.lang.String subscriberName)
      Register a generic subscriber to the stream. Strict message ordering is guaranteed to be the same of submission
      Parameters:
      subscriber - Java Flow compliant subscriber
      bufferSize - Consumer buffer. Updates messages exceeding this buffer size will cause a drop or a wait signal for the producer, according to the subscription type
      backpressureTimeout - For how long the subscription should attempt to deliver an update to the subscriber.
      asyncBackpressurer - the executor to use for async delivery, supporting creation of at least one independent thread
      subscriberName - This name must be unique and if deterministic it allows cold replay

    • backpressurableSubmit

      public java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage<java.lang.Void> backpressurableSubmit​(PayloadT message)
      Submit a new message to the feed. The delivery order among the subscribers is not predictable or consistent. If producer wants to regulate the production rate according to the consumers speed (flow regulation backpressuring) the next message has to be sent when the previous one has been delivered. Strict message ordering is guaranteed to be the same of submission. This call is never blocking.
      Parameters:
      message - the message that should be propagated to the subscribers
      Returns:
      a CompletionsStage that will be marked ad complete when the message has been delivered to all the subscribers
